2024/02/MY24-Sight-A-Framekit-Black-Gold-Side-Profile-TP-Large-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MY24-Sight-A-Framekit-Black-Gold-Side-Profile-TP-Large-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MY24-Sight-A-Framekit-Black-Gold-Side-Profile-TP-Large-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MY24-Sight-A-Framekit-Black-Gold-Side-Profile-TP-Large-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MY24-Sight-A-Framekit-Black-Gold-Side-Profile-TP-Large-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MY24-Sight-A-Framekit-Black-Gold-Side-Profile-TP-Large.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After 12 years in the Norco lineup, the Sight is still the do-it-all-mountain beast with 150mm rear travel and 160mm front. Offered in C1, C2 MX, C3 MX, and a C SE carbon build at the high end, the Sight A1 MX and A2 MX are the more affordable aluminum options with hydroformed tubes and smooth welds. The lightest you’ll find the Sight is the C SE with RockShox Ultimate Flight Attendant and XO Eagle Transmission at 33.3 lbs / 15.1kg for an S3.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Norco Optic</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MY24-Optic-C1-29-Black-Side-Profile-TPb-Large.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MY24-Optic-C1-29-Black-Side-Profile-TPb-Large-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"MY24 Optic C1 29 Black Side Profile TPb Large\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MY24-Optic-C1-29-Black-Side-Profile-TPb-Large-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MY24-Optic-C1-29-Black-Side-Profile-TPb-Large-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MY24-Optic-C1-29-Black-Side-Profile-TPb-Large-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MY24-Optic-C1-29-Black-Side-Profile-T